TRIP COMMENTS: Santa Barbara Audubon Society field trip. Birding with Jack Sanford and five others; the lake was at or near capacity. Conditions: overcast, intermittent drizzle, approx. 60 deg F, calm. Coverage: This is the former ostrich ranch, the private rance on the peninsula between the east end of Cachuma Kake and Arrowhead Island. After birding the farm pond that is visible from 154, we parked near the enclosed horse corral/arena and walked east to the east end of the lake. From here, we followed the path above the lake, first walking north, then gradually west along the narrows, and south along the shore opposite Arrowhead Island, before turning southeast and then east back to the cars.

SPECIES COMMENTS: riding the ridge at 5000' between Sand and Grapevine Canyons; This has been a great spring for Ospreys.  Three more  Ospreys were seen this month.  The first was seen Apr 2 soaring over a 5000' ridge that separates Grapevine from Sand Canyon (SS, SE).  Amazingly enough this bird was heading west and looked like it was headed over the Sierra somewhere in the vicinity of Owen's Peak.  The second was hunting over Lark Seep Apr 4 (SS).  The third was soaring over B Mountain Apr 13 (SS).  The Osprey was new for all three locations - Grapevine # 90, Sand #133, and Lark Seep #93.
